  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "Whether a CCTV system works during a power cut depends on its power supply setup. Here are a few scenarios:\n\n1. **No Backup Power**: Most conventional CCTV cameras require power to operate. If they are directly connected to the main power supply, they will not function during a power cut.\n\n2. **Battery-Powered Cameras**: Some modern wireless cameras come with built-in rechargeable batteries. These can continue to operate during a power cut, but only for a limited period depending on the battery life.\n\n3. **Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS)**: If a CCTV system is connected to a UPS, it can continue functioning for a certain amount of time during a power outage. This is a common setup for business and critical installations.\n\n4. **Solar-Powered Cameras**: Some CCTV systems are equipped with solar panels that can provide power independently of the grid. As long as there is sufficient sunlight, they can continue operating during a power cut.\n\n5. **Generators**: Premises equipped with backup generators can maintain power to their CCTV systems as long as the generator is running.\n\nTo ensure continuous operation during power cuts, it's advisable to use either a UPS, battery backup, or solar power solutions tailored to the specific needs of the security system.",
